headline: First Solar Stock Falls 15%. Earnings Were So Not Good.
summary: First Solar  was down 15% Wednesday after issuing downside revenue guidance for the 2026 fiscal year.  The solar panel maker expects fiscal 2026 revenue in a range of $4.9 billion to $5.2 billion, which is below analysts’ expectations for $6.16 billion, according to FactSet.  The solar panel maker reported fourth-quarter earnings of $4.84 a share, 30 cents below the average analyst estimate as tracked by FactSet.
